3ei
); ‘as’ and ‘s’ presents; Abd III without Mc on A3, two Mc on area A4 (a 2 and a 3 ) and one Mc on A5 (m 3 ), ‘s’ between m 6 and p 6 , ‘ms’ interior; Abd IV without Mc on A6 area, 2–3 Mc on A7 (A 2 , A 3 and B 3 ; A 2 absent asymmetrically in one specimen ), two on A8 (A 4 and B 4 ), A9 with one Mc (B 5 ), A10 with two Mc (A 6 and B 6 ); sensillar formula similar to the rest of Entomobryidae : 2,2/1,2,2,12–13,3; microsensillar formula: 1,0/1,0,1.
